==English==

====Hyphenation====
dough&middot;nut

===Alternative spellings===
*[[donut]] (''US'')

===Noun===
'''doughnut''', plural '''[[doughnuts]]''' (''British spelling'')

# A deep-fried piece of dough or batter, commonly made a [[toroidal]] or [[ellipsoidal]] shape and mixed with various [[sweeteners]] and [[flavourings]], and sometimes filled with [[jam]], [[custard]] or [[cream]].
# Anything in the shape of [[torus]].
# A peel-out or [[skid-mark]] in the shape of doughnut or toroid; a 360-degree skid.
# (''derogatory slang'') A fat person.
#:''Hey doughnut! Get over here.''
# A spare automoblie tire, usually stored in the trunk, that is smaller than a full sized tire and is only intended for temporary use. 

====Synonyms====
*(''anything in the shape of a torus''): [[ring]], [[torus]]
*(''fat person''): [[Swiss roll]]

